        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 3:44PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Ozona, moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
The Intersection Of Ranch Road 2083 And Highway 405 and The
Intersection Of Highway 163 And Ranch Road 1973.

This includes Interstate 10 between Mile Markers 352 and 362.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
